{"name": "uritemplate", "metadata": {"name": "uritemplate", "version": "4.1.1", "classifiers": ["Development Status :: 5 - Production/Stable", "Intended Audience :: Developers", "License :: OSI Approved", "License :: OSI Approved :: Apache Software License", "License :: OSI Approved :: BSD License", "Programming Language :: Python", "Programming Language :: Python :: 3", "Programming Language :: Python :: 3.10", "Programming Language :: Python :: 3.6", "Programming Language :: Python :: 3.7", "Programming Language :: Python :: 3.8", "Programming Language :: Python :: 3.9", "Programming Language :: Python :: Implementation :: CPython"], "home_page": "https://uritemplate.readthedocs.org", "license": "BSD 3-Clause License or Apache License, Version 2.0", "documentation_url": null, "dependencies": [], "summary": "Implementation of RFC 6570 URI Templates", "upload_time": 1634123712}, "documentation": ["# uritemplate\n\n[Documentation] -- [GitHub] -- [Travis-CI]\n\nSimple python library to deal with [URI Templates]. The API looks like\n\n```python\nfrom uritemplate import URITemplate, expand\n\n# NOTE: URI params must be strings not integers\n\ngist_uri = 'https://api.github.com/users/sigmavirus24/gists{/gist_id}'\nt = URITemplate(gist_uri)\nprint(t.expand(gist_id='123456'))\n# => https://api.github.com/users/sigmavirus24/gists/123456\n\n# or\nprint(expand(gist_uri, gist_id='123456'))\n\n# also\nt.expand({'gist_id': '123456'})\nprint(expand(gist_uri, {'gist_id': '123456'}))\n```\n\nWhere it might be useful to have a class\n\n```python\nimport requests\n\nclass GitHubUser(object):\n    url = URITemplate('https://api.github.com/user{/login}')\n    def __init__(self, name):\n        self.api_url = url.expand(login=name)\n        response = requests.get(self.api_url)\n        if response.status_code == 200:\n            self.__dict__.update(response.json())\n```\n\nWhen the module containing this class is loaded, `GitHubUser.url` is\nevaluated and so the template is created once. It's often hard to notice in\nPython, but object creation can consume a great deal of time and so can the\n`re` module which uritemplate relies on. Constructing the object once should\nreduce the amount of time your code takes to run.\n\n## Installing\n\n```\npip install uritemplate\n```\n\n## License\n\nModified BSD [license]\n\n[documentation]: https://uritemplate.readthedocs.io/\n[github]: https://github.com/python-hyper/uritemplate\n[license]: https://github.com/python-hyper/uritemplate/blob/master/LICENSE\n[travis-ci]: https://travis-ci.org/python-hyper/uritemplate\n[uri templates]: https://tools.ietf.org/html/rfc6570\n"], "modules": [{"name": "uritemplate", "documentation": ["# uritemplate\n\nURI templates implemented as close to {rfc}`6570` as possible\n\nSee <http://uritemplate.rtfd.org/> for documentation\n\n```\ncopyright\n\n2013 Ian Stapleton Cordasco\n\nsource:2: (INFO/1) Enumerated list start value not ordinal-1: \"c\" (ordinal 3)\n\nlicense\n\nModified BSD Apache License (Version 2.0), see LICENSE for more details\nand either LICENSE.BSD or LICENSE.APACHE for the details of those specific\nlicenses\n```\n"], "functions": [], "variables": [{"name": "uritemplate.__title__", "type": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "uritemplate.__author__", "type": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "uritemplate.__license__", "type": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "uritemplate.__copyright__", "type": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "uritemplate.__version__", "type": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "uritemplate.__version_info__", "type": null, "documentation": []}], "classes": [], "exports": [{"name": "uritemplate.expand", "xref": {"fqname": "uritemplate.api.expand", "project": null}}, {"name": "uritemplate.partial", "xref": {"fqname": "uritemplate.api.partial", "project": null}}, {"name": "uritemplate.URITemplate", "xref": {"fqname": "uritemplate.api.URITemplate", "project": null}}, {"name": "uritemplate.variables", "xref": {"fqname": "uritemplate.api.variables", "project": null}}]}, {"name": "uritemplate.orderedset", "documentation": ["From: https://github.com/ActiveState/code/blob/master/recipes/Python/576696_OrderedSet_with_Weakrefs/  # noqa"], "functions": [], "variables": [], "classes": [{"name": "uritemplate.orderedset.Link", "bases": [], "methods": [], "class_variables": [{"name": "uritemplate.orderedset.Link.__slots__", "type": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "uritemplate.orderedset.Link.prev", "type": {"name": "Link", "xref": {"fqname": "uritemplate.orderedset.Link", "project": null}, "params": null}, "documentation": []}, {"name": "uritemplate.orderedset.Link.next", "type": {"name": "Link", "xref": {"fqname": "uritemplate.orderedset.Link", "project": null}, "params": null}, "documentation": []}, {"name": "uritemplate.orderedset.Link.key", "type": {"name": "str", "xref": {"fqname": "functions.str", "project": "--std--"}, "params": null}, "documentation": []}], "instance_variables": [], "inner_classes": [], "documentation": ["Representation of one item in a doubly-linked list."]}, {"name": "uritemplate.orderedset.OrderedSet", "bases": [], "methods": [{"name": "uritemplate.orderedset.OrderedSet.__init__", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "self", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "iterable", "type": {"name": "t.Optional", "xref": {"fqname": "typing.Optional", "project": "--std--"}, "params": [{"name": "t.Iterable", "xref": {"fqname": "typing.Iterable", "project": "--std--"}, "params": [{"name": "str", "xref": {"fqname": "functions.str", "project": "--std--"}, "params": null}]}]}, "default": "..."}], "returns": null, "documentation": ["Big-O running times for all methods are the same as for regular sets.", "The internal self.__map dictionary maps keys to links in a doubly linked", "list. The circular doubly linked list starts and ends with a sentinel", "element. The sentinel element never gets deleted (this simplifies the", "algorithm). The prev/next links are weakref proxies (to