tps://api.github.com{/end}')\n```\n"]}], "class_variables": [], "instance_variables": [], "inner_classes": [], "documentation": ["This parses the template and will be used to expand it.\n\nThis is the most important object as the center of the API.\n\nExample:\n\n```\nfrom uritemplate import URITemplate\nimport requests\n\n\nt = URITemplate(\n    'https://api.github.com/users/sigmavirus24/gists{/gist_id}'\n)\nuri = t.expand(gist_id=123456)\nresp = requests.get(uri)\nfor gist in resp.json():\n    print(gist['html_url'])\n```\n\nPlease note:\n\n```\nstr(t)\n# 'https://api.github.com/users/sigmavirus24/gists{/gistid}'\nrepr(t)  # is equivalent to\n# URITemplate(str(t))\n# Where str(t) is interpreted as the URI string.\n```\n\nAlso, `URITemplates` are hashable so they can be used as keys in\ndictionaries.\n"]}], "exports": []}, {"name": "uritemplate.variable", "documentation": ["uritemplate.variable\n====================\n\nThis module contains the URIVariable class which powers the URITemplate class.\n\nWhat treasures await you:\n\n- URIVariable class\n\nYou see a hammer in front of you.\nWhat do you do?\n>"], "functions": [{"name": "uritemplate.variable.is_list_of_tuples", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "value", "type": {"name": "t.Any", "xref": {"fqname": "typing.Any", "project": "--std--"}, "params": null}, "default": null}], "returns": {"name": "t.Tuple", "xref": {"fqname": "typing.Tuple", "project": "--std--"}, "params": [{"name": "bool", "xref": {"fqname": "functions.bool", "project": "--std--"}, "params": null}, {"name": "t.Optional", "xref": {"fqname": "typing.Optional", "project": "--std--"}, "params": [{"name": "t.Sequence", "xref": {"fqname": "typing.Sequence", "project": "--std--"}, "params": [{"name": "t.Tuple", "xref": {"fqname": "typing.Tuple", "project": "--std--"}, "params": [{"name": "str", "xref": {"fqname": "functions.str", "project": "--std--"}, "params": null}, {"name": "ScalarVariableValue", "xref": {"fqname": "ScalarVariableValue", "